<text top="66" left="687" width="68" height="16" font="1">Rev. No. 0</text>
<text top="48" left="428" width="150" height="16" font="1">BURNER DATASHEET</text>
<text top="105" left="140" width="519" height="19" font="6">New Notes for Burner Oil gun replacement (EIL Job No. C238 of 2026):</text>
<text top="108" left="659" width="4" height="16" font="7">.</text>
<text top="140" left="140" width="663" height="16" font="7">1. This datasheet is preparaed primarily intended to increase capacity of the existing burner oil guns by 10% i.e. to </text>
<text top="157" left="165" width="270" height="16" font="7">maximum heat liberation of 3.916 MMKCal/hr.</text>
<text top="189" left="140" width="11" height="16" font="7">2.</text>
<text top="189" left="170" width="505" height="16" font="7">The oil gun of the existing burners shall be replaced with an 10% higher capacity oil gun.</text>
<text top="205" left="170" width="607" height="16" font="7">Fuels shall be same as existing, with new fuels corresponding to current operating scenario added as below:</text>
<text top="669" left="140" width="663" height="16" font="7">3. OEM/ Oil gun supplier shall review the firebox sketch and guarantee that there shall be no flame impingement </text>
<text top="685" left="139" width="273" height="16" font="7">on the radiant tubes at maximum heat liberation.</text>
<text top="734" left="140" width="11" height="16" font="7">4.</text>
<text top="734" left="166" width="423" height="16" font="7">Revised sketch of Radiant Box may be referred from the drawing attached.</text>
</page>
